Best and worst: The most British polling stations in pictures

2016-06-23

The British public are expected to turn up in their thousands to vote in the EU referendum. Polling stations are open until 10pm, and with true British respect for the queuing system, if you are in line before 10, you will be allowed to vote.

Here are the most British examples of democracy in action, in pictures taken around the UK on Thursday.

If you think your polling station should be added to this, email us – [email protected] Or tweet us @theipaper – Or message us on Facebook.

